  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Engineer",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a Technical Engineer with hands-on experience in RFID solutions, and turnstile/access control systems. The successful candidate will be responsible for installation, system integration, testing, commissioning, and maintenance of security and tracking solutions across multiple project sites.</p><p>This role involves both on-site and technical support work, working closely with project managers, clients, and vendors to ensure successful project delivery.<br /></p><p>Key Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Deploy and support RFID systems (UHF/HF), including readers, antennas, tags, and middleware</li><li>Install and integrate turnstile systems (tripod, flap barrier, full-height) with access control, RFID, and biometric.</li><li>Conduct site surveys, system setup, cabling checks, and troubleshooting</li><li>Perform system testing, commissioning, and user acceptance testing (UAT)</li><li>Provide technical support, fault rectification, and preventive maintenance</li><li>Prepare technical documentation such as method statements, test reports, and as-built drawings</li><li>Liaise with customers, subcontractors, and vendors during project execution</li><li>Ensure compliance with safety procedures, security standards, and project requirements</li></ul><p><br />Requirements:</p><ul><li>Diploma or Certificate in Electrical, Electronics, IT, or related discipline</li><li>Minimum 2–5 years of relevant experience in RFID, access control, or turnstile systems</li><li>Hands-on knowledge of: IP networking (TCP/IP, PoE, switches) and VMS platforms, RFID readers, antennas, and tag performance, Turnstile and access control integration</li><li>Able to read wiring diagrams and technical drawings</li><li>Willing to work on-site and outside office hours when required</li><li>Possess good troubleshooting and problem-solving skills</li><li>Team player with good communication skills</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
